<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-02-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-02-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/4164 Suppl.: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-02-16T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 16,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>14. Department’s telegram No. 12, February 1, 5 p.m. If Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs has not yet taken occasion to resolve the ambiguity as
                            to Japanese Government’s attitude towards consortium loan to China you
                            will please consult with British Ambassador and take early opportunity
                            to see Minister and inquire as to Japanese Government’s position.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>